Customers are what businesses depend on to help them climb the ladder of success. If a crew has been properly trained how to serve customers but fail to do their job then steps should be taken like warnings or counseling then leave without pay or suspension. If the issue has not been settled then a replacement is always available. Losing customers will not bring you to the top. It makes business bad, your customers seek out a better place, and it also brings embarrassment to the community being seeved. Everyone has issues but rudeness coming from employees should never be tolerated. When I mentioned about placing the order by phone, the employee was very disrespectful. No I have no experience in business management, but I do have morals, manners, and knowledge on how to be tolerant and professional. These are just a few things that can be learned by looking around, listening, having a heart to feel and sharing a few kind words can make a huge difference in a workplace. Also teamwork and open communication are the most important when it comes to serving the public. Don't forget having a bit of patience. It is surely a virtue that would lead to success in the long run.
